"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519900","Department of Health","false","2016-05-26","<p>The number of people who have been diagnosed with endometriosis is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>The table below shows finished hospital admission episodes (FAEs) with a primary diagnosis of endometriosis, for the year 2014-15. The data only include diagnoses of endometriosis where there was a hospital admission. There may be further cases of the condition that were diagnosed and treated in another healthcare setting, including hospital outpatient services.</p><p> </p><p>These data are not counts of people, as the same person may have been admitted to hospital on more than one occasion. These data are based on the patient’s normal home address.</p><p> </p><p>Count of FAEs for female patients with a primary diagnosis of endometriosis, for Sunderland Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG), North East England Government Office Region (GOR), and England in 2014-15:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Region of residence</p></td><td><p>FAEs</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sunderland CCG</p></td><td><p>109</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North East GOR</p></td><td><p>718</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td><p>18,011</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-05-26T11:08:39.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519900/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519900/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519900/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-20","Endometriosis: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many women have been diagnosed with endometriosis in (a) Sunderland, (b) the North East and (c) England.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","37718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519901","Department of Health","false","2016-05-26","<p>The usual practice of the Department's National Institute for Health Research (NIHR) and of the Medical Research Council is not to ring-fence funds for expenditure on particular topics: research proposals in all areas compete for the funding available.</p><p>The Department's NIHR welcomes funding applications for research into any aspect of human health, including endometriosis. These applications are subject to peer review and judged in open competition, with awards being made on the basis of the importance of the topic to patients and health and care services, value for money and scientific quality. In all disease areas, the amount of NIHR funding depends on the volume and quality of scientific activity. The NIHR has funded a number of studies relevant to the condition.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-05-26T08:26:35.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519901/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519901/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519901/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-20","Endometriosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has for the future level of funding for researching the causes of and treatments for endometriosis.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","37719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519902","Department of Health","false","2016-05-26","<p>Community pharmacy is a vital part of the National Health Service. We want to see a high quality community pharmacy service that is properly integrated into primary care and public health in line with the Five Year Forward View.</p><p>We want to make pharmacists a pivotal part of primary care for all patient groups, including the elderly and vulnerable, by increasing the number who bring their skills to general practitioner (GP) practices, care homes, urgent care and public health settings. We have consulted on how best to introduce a Pharmacy Integration Fund to help transform how pharmacists, their teams and community pharmacy will operate in the NHS, bringing clear benefits to patients and the public.</p><p>Our aim is to ensure that those community pharmacies upon which people depend continue to thrive. We are consulting on the introduction of a Pharmacy Access Scheme, which will provide more NHS funds to certain pharmacies compared with others, considering factors such as location and the health needs of the local population.</p><p>The community pharmacy proposals for 2016/17 and beyond, on which we have consulted, are being considered in respect to the public sector equality duty, the family test and relevant duties of the Secretary of State under the NHS Act 2006.</p><p>An impact assessment will be completed to inform final decisions and published in due course.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","37711","2016-05-26T14:07:38.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519902/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519902/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519902/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-20","Pharmacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of his proposals for the future of community pharmacy on care for elderly people.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","37710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519903","Department of Health","false","2016-05-26","<p>Community pharmacy is a vital part of the National Health Service. We want to see a high quality community pharmacy service that is properly integrated into primary care and public health in line with the Five Year Forward View.</p><p>We want to make pharmacists a pivotal part of primary care for all patient groups, including the elderly and vulnerable, by increasing the number who bring their skills to general practitioner (GP) practices, care homes, urgent care and public health settings. We have consulted on how best to introduce a Pharmacy Integration Fund to help transform how pharmacists, their teams and community pharmacy will operate in the NHS, bringing clear benefits to patients and the public.</p><p>Our aim is to ensure that those community pharmacies upon which people depend continue to thrive. We are consulting on the introduction of a Pharmacy Access Scheme, which will provide more NHS funds to certain pharmacies compared with others, considering factors such as location and the health needs of the local population.</p><p>The community pharmacy proposals for 2016/17 and beyond, on which we have consulted, are being considered in respect to the public sector equality duty, the family test and relevant duties of the Secretary of State under the NHS Act 2006.</p><p>An impact assessment will be completed to inform final decisions and published in due course.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","37710","2016-05-26T14:07:38.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519903/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519903/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519903/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-20","Pharmacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of his proposals for the future of community pharmacy on care for vulnerable patients.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","37711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519904","Department of Health","false","2016-05-26","<p>The procedure governing a country’s departure from the European Union is set out in Article 50 of the Treaty on European Union. This provides for a period of two years for the negotiation of exit terms. EU law would continue to apply to the departing Member State until the Article 50 agreement had entered into force, or for two years if no agreement had been reached and no extension to the two year period had been granted. A request for an extension could only be granted with the unanimous agreement of the remaining Member States. The Government's position is that the United Kingdom will be stronger, safer and better off remaining in a reformed EU.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-05-26T14:09:39.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519904/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519904/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519904/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-20","Medical Treatments Abroad: Europe","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of whether UK citizens would retain the automatic right to hold the European Health Insurance Card during the period prior to the completion of Article 50 negotiations relating to the Lisbon Treaty in the event of the UK voting to leave the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Ben Bradshaw","Exeter","Mr Ben Bradshaw","37721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519905","Department of Health","false","2016-05-26","<p>The information requested is not collected centrally.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-05-26T08:37:48.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519905/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519905/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519905/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-20","Endometriosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he makes of the proportion of women with endometriosis who do not receive the correct (a) diagnosis of and (b) treatment for that condition.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","37737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519906","Department of Health","false","2016-05-25","<p>We have had not had recent discussions at Ministerial level or with external organisations on changing the entitlement to free prescriptions for those age 60 and over who are in full time employment.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-05-25T10:07:31.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519906/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519906/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519906/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-20","Prescriptions: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent discussions he has had with (a) his ministerial colleagues and (b) external organisations on the provision of free prescriptions for those over the age of 60 who are in full-time employment.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","37736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519907","Department of Health","false","2016-05-25","<p>We have been consulting on proposals for community pharmacy in 2016/17 and beyond.</p><p>Throughout the consultation period we have remained open to new ideas and suggestions both from the Pharmaceutical Services Negotiating Committee (PSNC) and from other stakeholders.</p><p>We have welcomed the publication of PSNC’s counter proposal on 26 April 2016. This has enabled these ideas to be discussed with other key stakeholders.</p><p>The public phase of the consultation ended on 24 May 2016. The Department, supported by NHS England, will continue to discuss the proposals in confidence, with the PSNC and hold a final round of confidential discussions with other key pharmacy stakeholders.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-05-25T10:05:00.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519907/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519907/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519907/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-20","Pharmacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of the Pharmaceutical Services Negotiating Committee's counter-proposal to the Government's plans for the future of community pharmacy, published in April 2016.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","37713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519908","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2016-05-31","<p>Information regarding claims and awards in respect of each particular disease/vaccine is unavailable. This is because this information is not collected or collated.</p><p> </p><p>The Vaccine Damage Payments Unit administers the Scheme but do not collate information about vaccinations given to those claiming or receiving a payment under the scheme. As a number of vaccinations are often given in close proximity, often on the same day, it is not always possible to state categorically which has caused the adverse reaction. Such data is not required for the administration of the scheme.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2016-05-31T14:16:58.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519908/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519908/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519908/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2016-05-20","Whooping Cough: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many (a) claims and (b) payments were made following claim approval for vaccine damage for whooping cough in each year since 2003.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","37766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519909","Department of Health","false","2016-05-25","<p>This is a matter for local National Health Service commissioners.</p><p>NHS England advises that Mansfield and Ashfield Clinical Commissioning Group’s contract with the caretaker providers has been established on the same basis as the previous contract with Central Nottinghamshire Clinical Services.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-05-25T15:47:46.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519909/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519909/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519909/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-20","Health Services: Nottinghamshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether Nottingham Emergency Medical Services and Nottinghamshire Healthcare NHS Trust will receive further funding from the Government to provide any extra services in Ashfield and Mansfield required as a result of Central Nottinghamshire Clinical Services no longer providing such services.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","37759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519910","Department of Health","false","2016-05-27","<p>Our Childhood Obesity Strategy, which will be launched in the summer, will look at everything that contributes to a child becoming overweight and obese.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-05-27T11:53:17.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519910/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519910/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519910/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-20","Obesity: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what account he plans to take of dietary inequality and food insecurity in the planned childhood obesity strategy.","false","Biography information for Dr Eilidh Whiteford","Banff and Buchan","Dr Eilidh Whiteford","37727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519911","Department of Health","false","2016-05-25","<p><strong> </strong></p><p>There is no central collection of data on the average and longest wait for a carer’s assessment after an initial request was made since the introduction of the Carers Act 2014. Nor is data collected centrally on the number of people currently on the waiting list for a carer’s assessment.</p><p> </p><p>Data on the number of carers assessed during the financial year 2014-15 by local authority is attached. It should be noted that these figures include both joint and separate assessments from the cared for person. The source for this data is Short and Long Term Support (SALT), England 2014-15. This return is collected and published by the Health and Social Care Information Centre.</p><p>Link to SALT:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.hscic.gov.uk/catalogue/PUB18663" target="_blank">http://www.hscic.gov.uk/catalogue/PUB18663</a></p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","37763 ; 37765","2016-05-25T10:10:30.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519911/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519911/answer","PQ37765 table.xlsx","PQ37765 table.xlsx","Number of carers assessed 2014/15","Number of carers assessed 2014/15","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/519911/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-05-20","Carers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people are currently on the waiting list for a carers' assessment.","false","Biography information for Liz Kendall","Leicester West","Liz Kendall","37764"
